{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"edf9bcb2-9ef2-48ac-aa3f-0d29ec8dd65f","content":"Here are the common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core (`dotnet new`)**\n- `webapi` — minimal API or controller-based\n- Auth options: `--auth Individual` (Identity/local DB), `--auth IndividualB2C` (Azure AD B2C), `--auth SingleOrg` (Azure AD), `--auth Windows`\n\n**Node.js / Express**\n- Use `express-generator` or scaffold manually\n- Auth: Passport.js (local, OAuth, JWT), express-jwt, or Auth0 SDK\n\n**Python / FastAPI**\n- `fastapi` with `python-jose` for JWT, or `authlib` for OAuth2\n\n**General auth patterns:**\n| Pattern | Best for |\n|---|---|\n| JWT Bearer tokens | SPAs, mobile clients |\n| Cookie/session | Server-rendered apps |\n| OAuth2 / OIDC | Third-party login (Google, GitHub) |\n| API keys | Service-to-service |\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a specific project? If so, let me know the language/framework and auth type you prefer.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"38a5d8d0-b904-4583-a9d8-b934d761847b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - it's a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":310},"id":"a3a99a78-6fc5-4b00-9c4c-71051afdb0f7","timestamp":"2026-04-09T15:19:51.766Z","parentId":"cbe46c00-ce55-468d-a668-98c94e6e1fca"}
